    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't know about `p instructions` (`p ins`?).  If we really want it to be a special thing it could be `p cod` or something.  But I think I'd just change the default opcode printout to show a display of, say, 3 behind and 3 ahead (note: obviously that number would need to be tuned based on how the result looks), in addition to the current one, much like our default view of the source code doesn't just show the particular line we're on.\r\n\r\nIf that's not enough we could maybe add something for seeing the full disassembly, but I'd start by just expanding what we show by default.",
